{"questionId":"27707","questionHtml":"<p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext></math> in terms of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>α</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> In parts (a) and (b) of this question, candidates may consider either triangle AOD&nbsp;or triangle AOE&nbsp;and work correctly to obtain the answer. Side AD&nbsp;is interchangeable with side AE&nbsp;in the following MS.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>recognizing that the sum of the angles of a kite is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>O</mtext><mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>E</mtext><mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>·</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">α</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1A0</strong></em> if candidate uses degrees (i.e.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>O</mtext><mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>E</mtext><mover><mtext>A</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>+</mo><mtext>A</mtext><mover><mtext>D</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>α</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>·</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>360</mn><mo>°</mo></math>)&nbsp;and obtains&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>D</mtext><mover><mtext>O</mtext><mo>^</mo></mover><mtext>E</mtext><mo>=</mo><mn>180</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">α</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27707","referenceCode":"22N.2.SL.TZ0.8b.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find DO^E in terms of α.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}